@startuml stream-parameter-values-cancellation
' Requirements: L2-ARC-002
' Source: docs/specs/archive/L1.md, docs/specs/archive/L2.md
title Parameter replay stream - rejection and client cancellation
autonumber
actor "Operator/Client" as Client
participant "HTTP API" as HTTP
participant "StreamParameterValues Handler" as Handler
database "Parameter Archive Store" as Store

Client -> HTTP : POST /api/archive/{instance}:streamParameterValues\n{ ids[], start, stop }
activate HTTP

alt invalid request body (empty ids, missing or inverted start/stop)
  HTTP -> HTTP : validate request body
  HTTP --> Client : 400 Bad Request { validation errors }\n(no stream is opened)
else client disconnects mid-stream
  HTTP -> Handler : StreamParameterValuesQuery(instance, ids, start, stop)
  activate Handler
  Handler -> Store : openCursor(pids, start, stop)
  activate Store
  HTTP --> Client : 200 OK, chunked stream opened
  loop streaming batches
    Handler -> Store : nextBatch()
    Store --> Handler : batch of parameter values
    Handler --> HTTP : emit batch
    HTTP --> Client : chunk { parameter data }
  end
  Client -x HTTP : TCP connection closed by client
  HTTP -> Handler : signal cancellation token
  Handler -> Store : close cursor, release read resources
  deactivate Store
  Handler --> HTTP : stream aborted
  deactivate Handler
end
deactivate HTTP

note right of Handler
  Detailed-design guardrails for L2-ARC-002: a chunked
  server stream must terminate cleanly on client
  disconnect so archive cursors and buffers are not
  leaked across long replay intervals.
end note
@enduml
